757
00:57:03.840 --> 00:57:09.769
Kostadis Roussos: Well, she, she, she's a… she… okay, so… so your intuition is that she's going… like, you…

758
00:57:11.430 --> 00:57:14.389
Kostadis Roussos: The best you can hope for is temporary leverage.

759
00:57:17.260 --> 00:57:18.200
Mike Hall: Right.

760
00:57:18.570 --> 00:57:19.780
Kostadis Roussos: Right, that's all I'm saying.

761
00:57:23.910 --> 00:57:33.370
Kostadis Roussos: So, what, so, okay, so she, so she, so she says this, that, that, that the matron mother was, was most interested in you.

762
00:57:34.120 --> 00:57:34.890
Mike Hall: Why?

763
00:57:35.820 --> 00:57:39.080
Kostadis Roussos: Okay.

764
00:57:39.080 --> 00:57:40.710
Ben Pfaff: I have a feeling that she didn't say.

765
00:57:48.590 --> 00:57:52.610
Ben Pfaff: But why would she usually be interested in someone?

766
00:57:57.230 --> 00:58:11.939
Kostadis Roussos: So, if you want to, look at… if you want to get the why, you're going to have to… you get the intuition, you're going to have to try to make… get some more leverage on her. Intimidate her, scare her, offer her something.

767
00:58:14.450 --> 00:58:16.389
Mike Hall: Like, that she gets to live?

768
00:58:19.520 --> 00:58:25.809
Thorin (Joe): If you want to intimidate her, we can threaten to actually leave her out, exposed to the bright, over bright sun.

769
00:58:26.060 --> 00:58:30.350
Gabe: Do you even need to? Because you're holding Dawnbringer, like, next to her head.

770
00:58:30.660 --> 00:58:33.970
Thorin (Joe): So maybe I tell Dawnbringer, like, be extra bright.

771
00:58:35.040 --> 00:58:38.080
Thorin (Joe): Shine, Dawnbringer, shine!

772
00:58:40.620 --> 00:58:51.210
Kostadis Roussos: Okay, and Grygum, do you, like, try to intimidate her as well? Like, you know, you are a half-orc, you know the stories of the drow and how they've oppressed your people for centuries and millennia.

773
00:58:52.480 --> 00:58:55.780
Ben Pfaff: I… I hand her the prayer beads and tell her to put them on.

774
00:58:57.460 --> 00:59:03.010
Kostadis Roussos: Like, just that. That actually… that actually freaks her out. Like, that, that…

775
00:59:03.890 --> 00:59:14.859
Kostadis Roussos: Like, all of a sudden, you know, she's part of a deeply… a religious cult, and, like, now she's, like, really worried. Like, when the priest hands over the beads, that actually is a moment of pure intimidation.

776
00:59:15.460 --> 00:59:20.690
Ben Pfaff: Yeah, I have a follow-up to it if necessary, but that seemed like a good start.

777
00:59:20.690 --> 00:59:28.720
Kostadis Roussos: Yeah, no, no, that was a very, she looks defeated, frustrated, annoyed…

778
00:59:28.830 --> 00:59:35.230
Kostadis Roussos: And goes, my matron believes that the one who paid, and she points to Daz.

779
00:59:36.470 --> 00:59:40.410
Kostadis Roussos: For him, will reveal themselves once he reaches the surface.

780
00:59:40.980 --> 00:59:42.900
Mike Hall: I'm on the surface of Toril.

781
00:59:43.050 --> 00:59:46.079
Kostadis Roussos: No, no, no, no, someone paid to protect you.

782
00:59:47.610 --> 00:59:50.540
Kostadis Roussos: We're looking for that person, not for you.

783
00:59:50.540 --> 00:59:52.210
Ben Pfaff: She is not wrong.

784
00:59:52.960 --> 00:59:56.389
Kostadis Roussos: So, my matron believes the one who paid for him

785
00:59:57.030 --> 01:00:00.059
Kostadis Roussos: Will reveal themselves once he reaches the surface.

786
01:00:00.250 --> 01:00:00.910
Kostadis Roussos: was picked.

787
01:00:00.910 --> 01:00:03.570
Mike Hall: So, we did, we did have some mercenaries help us.

788
01:00:03.730 --> 01:00:06.649
Kostadis Roussos: Yes, but we don't know who the mercenaries worked for.

789
01:00:08.610 --> 01:00:11.170
Kostadis Roussos: The mercenaries don't know who they worked for.

790
01:00:11.170 --> 01:00:20.440
Mike Hall: Right, so no one knows who they work for. So basically, you're treating me as, bait.

791
01:00:20.920 --> 01:00:28.519
Mike Hall: For your… in political… for your… Queen Mother's, political intrigue.

792
01:00:28.760 --> 01:00:34.390
Mike Hall: You're watching and observing so that when something happens to me, you can go report back what happened to me.

793
01:00:34.720 --> 01:00:39.859
Kostadis Roussos: Yes, because we are looking for the one who protect… who paid to have you protected.

794
01:00:40.540 --> 01:00:41.900
Mike Hall: Why do you care?

795
01:00:44.180 --> 01:00:47.990
Kostadis Roussos: She goes, the matron mother cares, and therefore I care. She doesn't have.

796
01:00:48.300 --> 01:00:59.030
Ben Pfaff: Perhaps, perhaps we could conduct an experiment to find these people who are following or attempting to protect us.

797
01:00:59.600 --> 01:00:59.960
Kostadis Roussos: Okay.

798
01:00:59.960 --> 01:01:00.720
Ben Pfaff: Or him.

799
01:01:02.440 --> 01:01:10.089
Ben Pfaff: I, I could, we, we could, find a place that, that's constricted, so…

800
01:01:10.300 --> 01:01:12.249
Ben Pfaff: They'd have to pass through…

801
01:01:12.360 --> 01:01:19.209
Ben Pfaff: As well, and then I could, I could inscribe a glyph of wording on it, and we could pass through and wait.

802
01:01:20.180 --> 01:01:37.090
Kostadis Roussos: That is a plan, but the insight you get is that somebody… so the House T’sarran, the insight you're getting from House T’sarran is that they are convinced that somebody, some bigger power is looking to protect Daz.

803
01:01:39.050 --> 01:01:43.250
Kostadis Roussos: Right? And they don't give a sh… and what you're also getting is they don't care about Daz, they care about that other power.

804
01:01:44.700 --> 01:01:54.790
Kostadis Roussos: Right, Daz is an 8th level wizard, yes, yes, he's powerful, but nobody cares about him. The person who paid to have him protected, now that's interesting, because Daz doesn't know why he was protected.

805
01:01:55.510 --> 01:01:56.240
Mike Hall: Right.

806
01:01:56.240 --> 01:02:03.679
Kostadis Roussos: So, whoever is protecting Daz knows why Daz is valuable, so what's important is Daz is the protector, not Daz.

807
01:02:04.150 --> 01:02:07.929
Ben Pfaff: That's why I was proposing that we try to find out who the protector is.

808
01:02:07.930 --> 01:02:17.700
Kostadis Roussos: The… the… the… the drow sort of laughs at that hypothesis, thinking that, you know, that… but he says you can try.

809
01:02:20.820 --> 01:02:23.599
Ben Pfaff: Now I'm curious why it would be a bad idea to try.

810
01:02:23.750 --> 01:02:38.289
Gabe: Well, the theory is that this person is nowhere near me, right? They've sent mercenaries, and they've provided funding to some other organization to find Dev. They're not following us, they're pulling strings somewhere.

811
01:02:38.290 --> 01:02:41.599
Kostadis Roussos: Yes, and so they're not, they're not gonna be literally present.

812
01:02:41.780 --> 01:02:45.149
Ben Pfaff: Okay, it's, at a higher level than I was thinking.

813
01:02:45.150 --> 01:02:54.690
Kostadis Roussos: Yes. So they're trying to see… they're trying to observe and collect information and see a slip-up by that person, and then collect more information and try to find out what's going on.

814
01:02:56.480 --> 01:03:03.670
Gabe: It occurs to me, though, we're basically trying to do the same thing. We all want to know who's trying to protect Daz.

815
01:03:03.960 --> 01:03:06.600
Mike Hall: And why, what their motivation is.

816
01:03:06.600 --> 01:03:12.319
Kostadis Roussos: Everybody's like, why is everybody interested in this, like, no-name drow, like…

817
01:03:12.320 --> 01:03:14.489
Mike Hall: Hey, hey, let's be careful.

818
01:03:15.010 --> 01:03:18.890
Ben Pfaff: Well then, there's only one solution. We need to kill Daz.

819
01:03:19.630 --> 01:03:22.560
Gabe: It's on the list, it's on the maybe list.

820
01:03:22.560 --> 01:03:26.350
Ben Pfaff: And then we'll find out who's, who's protecting him.

821
01:03:26.590 --> 01:03:28.650
Thorin (Joe): Do it, but make sure we can bring them back.

822
01:03:28.650 --> 01:03:30.599
Ben Pfaff: Oh, I have a Revivize spell.

823
01:03:30.600 --> 01:03:33.600
Thorin (Joe): Okay, you know, so that's just a temporary death. Yeah.

824
01:03:34.620 --> 01:03:36.169
Ben Pfaff: Just a death light.

825
01:03:36.550 --> 01:03:40.199
Thorin (Joe): Is Daz uncomfortable with this conversation?

826
01:03:41.020 --> 01:03:42.999
Ben Pfaff: The first thing you do is shoot the hostage.

827
01:03:43.000 --> 01:03:53.379
Kostadis Roussos: Alright. She then pauses and looks at you and says, don't think that killing me will stop the people spying on you. House T'sarran will keep sending people to follow you, blah blah blah.

828
01:03:53.380 --> 01:03:57.579
Ben Pfaff: I'm not relying on killing you, I'm relying on the prayer beads.

829
01:03:58.200 --> 01:03:59.400
Kostadis Roussos: Hello, soup now.

830
01:03:59.880 --> 01:04:00.700
Kostadis Roussos: Staff.

831
01:04:01.180 --> 01:04:02.000
Kostadis Roussos: Yes?

832
01:04:02.680 --> 01:04:04.850
Kostadis Roussos: She pauses for a minute.

833
01:04:05.500 --> 01:04:06.530
Kostadis Roussos: Huh.

834
01:04:07.600 --> 01:04:10.759
Kostadis Roussos: Well, so how about this? She pauses and says, look.

835
01:04:11.140 --> 01:04:17.709
Kostadis Roussos: Dude, for real, why are you yelling? Well, because I'm speaking too loudly. So what she… she turns around and says, hey, you know what?

836
01:04:18.140 --> 01:04:20.290
Kostadis Roussos: How about if we had a different arrangement?

837
01:04:20.590 --> 01:04:23.319
Kostadis Roussos: I need to keep spying on you, right?

838
01:04:24.880 --> 01:04:25.520
Gabe: No.

839
01:04:25.700 --> 01:04:32.179
Kostadis Roussos: Right? You guys want to find out who's following Daz, and I want to find out who's following Daz.

840
01:04:32.280 --> 01:04:44.170
Kostadis Roussos: And I want to keep my head, and you don't want to keep killing agents of House T'sarran. So what if… what if… what if we… we came to a compromise? That if I find anything, I tell you. If you find anything, you tell me.

841
01:04:44.890 --> 01:04:50.750
Thorin (Joe): Well, but we don't know that we want your matron to know who's following Daz.

842
01:04:51.380 --> 01:04:55.619
Kostadis Roussos: See, how come I'm known as the source of the voice, not the source of the voice.

843
01:04:56.350 --> 01:04:57.470
Thorin (Joe): I mean, both…

844
01:04:57.900 --> 01:04:59.409
Gabe: I mean, if it's not acceptable…

845
01:04:59.410 --> 01:05:00.470
Thorin (Joe): exclusive.

846
01:05:03.050 --> 01:05:05.469
Ben Pfaff: Are you having a lamb stew?

847
01:05:05.470 --> 01:05:06.190
Kostadis Roussos: Yes, sir.

848
01:05:06.210 --> 01:05:07.240
Ben Pfaff: Mmm.

849
01:05:07.240 --> 01:05:08.410
Kostadis Roussos: So,

850
01:05:08.600 --> 01:05:23.649
Kostadis Roussos: So, going back to the conversation, so… so she's like, well, you can try renegotiating the terms, but basically she's saying, you know, I… if I give… give giving information to House T'sarran, whatever I find that you keep, whatever you find, we share, and, you know.

851
01:05:25.990 --> 01:05:37.030
Ben Pfaff: Perhaps… perhaps you should not so much work with us as travel with us for a few days, and then we can all gather the same information.

852
01:05:37.030 --> 01:05:38.519
Kostadis Roussos: Well, that's exactly what I was suggesting.

853
01:05:38.520 --> 01:05:40.739
Thorin (Joe): Here's what we're gonna do. We're gonna take you with…

854
01:05:41.490 --> 01:05:43.930
Thorin (Joe): And we're gonna keep you bound.

855
01:05:44.030 --> 01:05:49.620
Thorin (Joe): But we're gonna treat you really well, so that when they send the next person to follow us, they'll know that you're a collaborator.

856
01:05:55.770 --> 01:05:59.280
Kostadis Roussos: Look, I was offering a plan that both… we both get what we wanted. I get to.

857
01:05:59.280 --> 01:06:09.719
Thorin (Joe): No, no, no, like, we're not sure that we want your matron to know what's going on here until we fully understand the situation, so we're committing to sharing of information that we don't know what that information is yet.

858
01:06:09.820 --> 01:06:14.370
Thorin (Joe): with parties that we don't know that well. So, you know, the whole thing is very sketchy.

859
01:06:15.960 --> 01:06:16.680
Mike Hall: Yeah.

860
01:06:17.640 --> 01:06:19.589
Gabe: Like, why should we trust you?

861
01:06:19.860 --> 01:06:26.110
Thorin (Joe): Yeah, that's the other thing, is that you find something, and then you just take off, and you never tell us, and, like, what are we gonna do? Like, go, like…

862
01:06:26.410 --> 01:06:28.639
Thorin (Joe): Rager, like, you know…

863
01:06:29.530 --> 01:06:30.769
Kostadis Roussos: I mean, that's all these are all good.

864
01:06:30.770 --> 01:06:36.619
Thorin (Joe): Oh, where do Drow gather anyways? It's not a keep. Is it Warren? Is it a, like…

865
01:06:37.050 --> 01:06:44.480
Thorin (Joe): frickin' a den? I mean, I don't know, whatever you guys hang out in, we're not gonna go raid that to kill you after this, right?

866
01:06:45.150 --> 01:06:46.330
Kostadis Roussos: So.

867
01:06:46.330 --> 01:06:48.040
Ben Pfaff: Unless we really have to.

868
01:06:48.830 --> 01:06:50.730
Thorin (Joe): I mean, we could, let's be clear.

869
01:06:50.910 --> 01:06:53.399
Kostadis Roussos: She's like, well.

870
01:06:53.560 --> 01:06:58.679
Kostadis Roussos: You know, I like the idea of me following you. As long as I keep submitting reports, nobody has to know.

871
01:07:00.850 --> 01:07:01.390
Gabe: Again.

872
01:07:01.390 --> 01:07:07.210
Thorin (Joe): But again, what's your motivation to actually share any information with us once you get it, versus just send the report in and then take off?

873
01:07:08.210 --> 01:07:12.649
Kostadis Roussos: Oh, I mean… We, we, we, we could, send the report together?

874
01:07:12.950 --> 01:07:13.870
Kostadis Roussos: I suspect…

875
01:07:13.870 --> 01:07:16.319
Ben Pfaff: This isn't a permanent arrangement, Thorin.

876
01:07:16.710 --> 01:07:26.099
Thorin (Joe): I'm just saying I don't buy it. I think, you know, the minute that she has the information she needs, she's off, and we get… we get jack shit.

877
01:07:26.380 --> 01:07:29.299
Ben Pfaff: But there might be some mutual benefits along the way.

878
01:07:29.530 --> 01:07:34.739
Ben Pfaff: And… and I just sort of pause and look at the prayer beads.

879
01:07:34.740 --> 01:07:35.430
Kostadis Roussos: Right.

880
01:07:37.200 --> 01:07:41.749
Thorin (Joe): Well, I mean, like, once she puts the prayer beads on, she can't take them off, right?

881
01:07:41.750 --> 01:07:42.889
Ben Pfaff: That's right.

882
01:07:43.890 --> 01:07:45.720
Kostadis Roussos: She's looking very nervous now.

883
01:07:46.460 --> 01:07:48.189
Thorin (Joe): I mean, that's just how these things work.

884
01:07:48.500 --> 01:07:48.820
Kostadis Roussos: Yes.

885
01:07:48.820 --> 01:07:50.430
Ben Pfaff: Tis the way of the curse.

886
01:07:50.600 --> 01:07:54.319
Kostadis Roussos: Right? She's, like, now very nervous.

887
01:07:55.930 --> 01:07:58.150
Kostadis Roussos: She looks, look.

888
01:07:58.520 --> 01:08:01.570
Kostadis Roussos: How about this? The only prob… so she goes.

889
01:08:01.770 --> 01:08:04.560
Kostadis Roussos: It's my understanding you're going to Candlekeep, yes?

890
01:08:06.710 --> 01:08:09.690
Thorin (Joe): Neither confirm nor deny those allegations.

891
01:08:09.690 --> 01:08:16.320
Kostadis Roussos: Well, if you're going to Candlekeep, we could make an arrangement. You drag me along to Candlekeep, and then hand me over to the Candlekeep guards.

892
01:08:18.660 --> 01:08:19.560
Thorin (Joe): Okay.

893
01:08:19.560 --> 01:08:21.180
Mike Hall: Okay… what's up?

894
01:08:21.189 --> 01:08:24.559
Kostadis Roussos: They put me in prison, and if I escape, I escape, and if I don't, I don't.

895
01:08:25.149 --> 01:08:28.119
Mike Hall: So they know how to escape that prison, is what they're telling us.

896
01:08:30.700 --> 01:08:33.909
Ben Pfaff: Well, I mean, turnabout is fair play, and we escape from their prison.

897
01:08:37.979 --> 01:08:45.809
Thorin (Joe): Yeah, but we were unfairly imprisoned. We were just, you know, sitting in the corner minding our own business, you know, sock mobbing, as it were.

898
01:08:47.609 --> 01:08:48.490
Kostadis Roussos: So…

899
01:08:49.170 --> 01:09:02.419
Kostadis Roussos: I mean, the other option is you can kill her, or you can just let her tire her up and move on, and let her try to catch up with you later. Head to Candlekeep, and once you're in Candlekeep, it'll be very… it'll be practically impossible for her to get in.

900
01:09:02.790 --> 01:09:07.489
Thorin (Joe): Can Glabbagool sort of, like, Engulf her and capture her and bring her along?

901
01:09:07.819 --> 01:09:08.429
Kostadis Roussos: I mean, yes.

902
01:09:08.430 --> 01:09:09.470
Ben Pfaff: for that, isn't he?

903
01:09:09.479 --> 01:09:11.599
Kostadis Roussos: No, he could do that, but he'd eat her.

904
01:09:11.689 --> 01:09:14.100
Thorin (Joe): Oh, I see, she would dissolve. Okay.

905
01:09:14.100 --> 01:09:16.639
Kostadis Roussos: No, so, so, like, the option of holding onto her…

906
01:09:16.649 --> 01:09:17.419
Ben Pfaff: for later.

907
01:09:17.840 --> 01:09:22.669
Kostadis Roussos: The option of holding… the one option is you could just leave her here and dash to Candlekeep.

908
01:09:24.620 --> 01:09:29.470
Kostadis Roussos: Right? What you've heard about Candlekeep is that it's basically an impregnable fortress.

909
01:09:30.649 --> 01:09:37.019
Thorin (Joe): Yeah, I don't… I mean, she's so confident she can escape, I don't think we want to be taking her into the stronghold, I'm just…

910
01:09:37.359 --> 01:09:41.460
Kostadis Roussos: Right. Yeah, so, yeah, so keeping her out might be the best solution for you.

911
01:09:41.830 --> 01:09:46.920
Thorin (Joe): But… the way we play this game is we always find the thing that you didn't expect, Kostadis.

912
01:09:46.920 --> 01:09:47.550
Ben Pfaff: Absolutely.

913
01:09:47.550 --> 01:09:48.170
Kostadis Roussos: I can't.

914
01:09:48.450 --> 01:09:53.830
Thorin (Joe): So that doesn't feel like we're making you dance, and so, you know, there's the game, and then there's the metagame.

915
01:09:55.550 --> 01:09:59.560
Gabe: So, do we still have those mushrooms of shrinking?

916
01:09:59.560 --> 01:10:00.230
Kostadis Roussos: Yes.

917
01:10:00.400 --> 01:10:01.870
Thorin (Joe): Well, we can put her in our pocket.

918
01:10:01.870 --> 01:10:04.060
Gabe: Exactly, we can have a new pocket paddle.

919
01:10:04.430 --> 01:10:05.020
Ben Pfaff: By the way.

920
01:10:05.020 --> 01:10:05.920
Mike Hall: like this.

921
01:10:10.510 --> 01:10:12.799
Kostadis Roussos: Okay, so you're going to reduce her.

922
01:10:14.090 --> 01:10:15.080
Mike Hall: Why not?

923
01:10:15.080 --> 01:10:16.530
Thorin (Joe): Well, first, we'll map her.

924
01:10:23.430 --> 01:10:33.229
Kostadis Roussos: Alright, you will map her. You will map her. Alright, so, so, so, you shove a mushroom down her throat, and she shrinks down to an appropriate size.

925
01:10:34.100 --> 01:10:37.299
Kostadis Roussos: She suddenly becomes very squeaky and indignant.

926
01:10:38.420 --> 01:10:39.979
Thorin (Joe): nickname her Polly Pocket.

927
01:10:42.180 --> 01:10:44.030
Thorin (Joe): It's very demeaning.

928
01:10:44.270 --> 01:10:46.230
Kostadis Roussos: Alright. Alright. Okay.

929
01:10:46.230 --> 01:10:48.449
Thorin (Joe): Now, do we have a mushroom to grow her again?

930
01:10:48.630 --> 01:10:50.089
Kostadis Roussos: Yes, you do. I think you do.

931
01:10:50.240 --> 01:10:57.529
Thorin (Joe): Alright, so we say she can escape through the holes of the, like, you know, the net that they're gonna try and keep her in, but she's not gonna be big.

932
01:10:57.820 --> 01:10:58.459
Kostadis Roussos: Oh, she actually…

933
01:10:58.460 --> 01:10:59.130
Thorin (Joe): He plays ball.

934
01:10:59.130 --> 01:11:03.000
Mike Hall: We can… we can put her in the bag of holding with Glabbagool, and he can just hold onto her.

935
01:11:04.350 --> 01:11:09.919
Thorin (Joe): Yeah, what does happen, like, when you're in the bag of holding with somebody, are you pressed up against them? Is there distance?

936
01:11:09.920 --> 01:11:10.950
Kostadis Roussos: Like, that's sort of, like.

937
01:11:10.950 --> 01:11:12.169
Thorin (Joe): There's, like, okay, so it's like.

938
01:11:12.170 --> 01:11:12.550
Mike Hall: like that.

939
01:11:12.550 --> 01:11:14.739
